# VibeStream: Startup Pre-Launch Plan

> **Goal**: Build the next YouTube/Netflix/Twitch for the future. Every decision should be made as if it will scale to 10 million users. Zero monthly AI API costs in launch phase.

## Audit Findings (Senior Dev Review)

### 🔴 Critical Issues
- **Sidebar has hardcoded mock users/videos** (`Ninja`, `Valkyrae`, `MrBeast Gaming`) pointing to `/watch/v1`, `/watch/v2` which are 404s.
- **VideoCard**: Thumbnail fallback uses an Unsplash URL — acceptable for dev but must be a local asset or R2-hosted fallback in production.
- **[formatViews](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx#33-40) function has a duplicate `if (n >= 1_000_000)` branch** — dead code bug.

### 🟡 UI / UX Notes
- Home page: Clean and solid. **Do not touch.** Featured hero, category bar, and grid are all correct.
- VideoCard: Good design. Minor fix needed: the `CheckCircle2` icon should only appear if `is_verified` is true in the profile (not always shown).
- Profile page needs a full overhaul — still showing mock channels.
- No mobile bottom nav visible on `/watch/[id]` pages.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Housekeeping (Code Quality)

#### [MODIFY] [components/Sidebar.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/Sidebar.tsx)
- Replace hardcoded `MOCK_USERS` and `MOCK_VIDEOS` with a real Supabase query to `subscriptions` and `videos`.
- Add a "Shorts" link to the nav.
- Show "No subscriptions yet" if the user has no subscriptions.

#### [MODIFY] [components/VideoCard.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx)
- Fix duplicate [formatViews](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoCard.tsx#33-40) branch.
- Only show `CheckCircle2` if `profile.is_verified === true`.
- Use a local R2-hosted placeholder image for fallback, not Unsplash.

---

### Phase 2: Creator Dashboard (`/studio/dashboard`)

A dedicated page for creators to manage their content, separate from profile settings.

#### [NEW] `app/studio/dashboard/page.tsx`
- **Header**: Creator stats (Total Views, Subscribers, Videos, Revenue).
- **Video Manager Table**: List all uploaded videos. Each row has: thumbnail, title, views, visibility badge, publish date, and action buttons (`Edit`, [Delete](file:///C:/GOLive/components/CommentSection.tsx#92-102)).
- **Quick Upload CTA**: "Upload Your Next Video" button.
- **AI Studio Link**: A prominent, Apple-style card link to `/studio/ai-studio`.

---

### Phase 3: AI Studio (`/studio/ai-studio`) — $0 Cost

Accessible ONLY from the Creator Dashboard or Studio menu. Not on the homepage or public pages.

**Design**: Apple-style — clean white card on dark background. A single primary action at a time (like the iPhone's "Open with" sheet). No clutter.

#### [NEW] `app/studio/ai-studio/page.tsx`
- **Step 1**: Creator selects one of their uploaded videos from a dropdown (populated via Supabase).
- **Step 2**: Click "✨ Analyze for Viral Moments". The UI shows a beautiful loading state.
- **Step 3**: Results show 2-4 timestamped "Vibe Moments" (e.g., `0:32 - 0:48: High-energy moment detected`).
- **Step 4**: Creator clicks "Clip & Post as Short" — the system trims the video to that segment.

#### [NEW] `app/api/ai-studio/analyze/route.ts`
- Accepts `{ videoId }` from the client.
- Fetches the video URL from Supabase.
- Calls the **Gemini 2.5 Flash API (Free Tier)** via `@google/genai` SDK.
- Sends the video URL and a structured prompt: *"Analyze this video for 2-4 moments most likely to go viral on short-form platforms. Look for: emotional peaks, surprising cuts, high-energy moments, first 3 seconds impact. Return JSON: `[{ startSec, endSec, reason, viralScore }]`"*.
- The Gemini free tier allows **250 requests/day** (1 frame/sec analysis) — sufficient for early launch.
- Returns the timestamped moments JSON to the client.

#### [NEW] `app/api/ai-studio/clip/route.ts`
- Accepts `{ videoUrl, startSec, endSec }`.
- Uses `fluent-ffmpeg` (already in the project) to trim the video locally.
- Uploads the trimmed clip to R2 under `shorts/{userId}/...`.
- Saves a new `videos` record with `is_short=true`.
- **$0 cost**: ffmpeg is open-source, no third-party service needed.

---

### Phase 4: Shorts / Reels

#### [NEW] [app/shorts/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Walt%20&%20Carter/.gemini/antigravity/playground/sonic-zenith/app/shorts/page.tsx)
- Full-viewport vertical snap-scrolling.
- Right-side floating action buttons (Like, Comment, Share, Subscribe).
- Auto-plays video on scroll, mutes on swipe-away.
- Queries `videos` WHERE `is_short = true`.

#### [MODIFY] [components/Sidebar.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/Sidebar.tsx)
- Add `{ icon: Film, label: "Shorts", path: "/shorts" }` to menu items.

#### [NEW] SQL
```sql
ALTER TABLE public.videos ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS is_short BOOLEAN DEFAULT false;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_videos_is_short ON public.videos(is_short) WHERE is_short = true;
```

